						               													<description>Alien Siege allows you to take part in the Marines&amp;rsquo; first encounter with the Aliens, in the chamber under the reactor. It is based in Aliens, the 1986 science fiction/horror film.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game may be played by one or more people. The player (or players) run the squad of 9 Marines; the Aliens pretty much run themselves, following an easy set of rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all the Marines have left the room through the doorway at the north end of the Map, or have been dragged off by the Aliens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is a simplified form of the standard Leading Edge system. Used, for example, in Phoenix Command.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The authorship of the game is not indicated, only the &amp;copy; of Leading Edge Games is mentioned, but quite possibly the authors are Barry Nakazono and David McKenzie, designers also of Phoenix Command and Aliens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Was included in Gateways Magazine #10.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
